com.autonomy.aci.client.transport.impl

Class AciResponseInputStreamImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.InputStream
      • java.io.FilterInputStream
        • com.autonomy.aci.client.transport.AciResponseInputStream
          • com.autonomy.aci.client.transport.impl.AciResponseInputStreamImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DecryptingAciResponseInputStreamImpl

    public class AciResponseInputStreamImpl
extends AciResponseInputStream
    This AciResponseInputStream implementation provides the ability to release a HttpClient connection when the stream has been read, even if the stream is being read by code that doesn't know where it's come from. It accomplishes this by using a FilterInputStream to pass all method calls to the ACI response InputStream and overrides the close() method, so that it can release the HTTP connection at the same time.

    This class is required to decorate the returned InputStream if the HttpClient has been setup to use the MultiThreadedHttpConnectionManager.
